author: 💛🤍💙LUSC Griffin🏆🏆🏆
text:
3/3 cont:
Leeds 3-0 Birmingham City,
Hillsborough (55,000).
#FACup Semi Final, #OnThisDay 1972.
#lufc Mick Jones (17th & 64 minutes), Peter Lorimer (24).
It was the 8th time United had won a major semi final tie in 8 seasons (bowing out of just 3) - earning a 4th trip to Wembley. https://t.co/Ogbul6PI8t

author: 💛🤍💙LUSC Griffin🏆🏆🏆
text:
2/3 cont #OnThisDay 1972.
Mick Jones opened the Leeds scoring on 17 minutes at Hillsborough & the game was made comfortable on 24 when Peter Lorimer scored United's second. MJ confirmed Don Revie's #lufc Aces would be at Wembley for the Centenary #FACup Final on 64 mins.
More 👇 https://t.co/zmlp5JNGNR

author: 💛🤍💙LUSC Griffin🏆🏆🏆
text:
A better cup game for Leeds #OnThisDay 1972 with the #FACup semi final win over Birmingham City at Hillsborough. League title chasing United's class outshine the brave Brummies who were on the cusp of promotion from D2.
#lufc 3-0 #bcfc, #OnThisDay.
More details & match reports 👇 https://t.co/rZ380CmUzB https://t.co/JIdVTQOYNH
